    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <div class="grid features tight">
      <div><h4>Day 1 — Idea Generation</h4><p>Drag-and-drop prompts and frameworks spark original concepts.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 2 — Characters</h4><p>Build a roster: protagonist, antagonist, side characters.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 3 — World & Setting</h4><p>Define locations, tone, rules, mood boards.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 4 — Conflict & Arcs</h4><p>Map goals, flaws, and turning points.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 5 — Beat Sheet</h4><p>Lay out a clear 3-act or Hero’s Journey structure.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 6 — Scene List</h4><p>Create scenes from beats; link to characters/locations.</p></div>
      <div><h4>Day 7 — Final Output</h4><p>Auto-compile your story outline; export PDF ready to pitch.</p></div>
    </div>
